Use the standard library
This is how to sort_array of array:
   Remember that n is array's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that j is 0
      Do this (diff of n and 1) times:
         When j is at most (diff of n and 2), then:
            When item j in array is more than item (sum of j and 1) in array, then:
               Remember that temp is item j in array
               Remember that item j in array is item (sum of j and 1) in array
               Remember that item (sum of j and 1) in array is temp
            End when
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is array
Now you know

>>> sort_array of []
[]
>>> sort_array of [5]
[5]
>>> sort_array of [2, 4, 3, 0, 1, 5]
[0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]